people shall be in peace.","year":-1023},{"id":"recGg57OMmlY1ilVe","ref":"2Sam.17.4","text":"And the saying pleased Absalom well, and all the elders of Israel.","year":-1023},{"id":"recJKaSknjv0ivhho","ref":"2Sam.17.5","text":"Then said Absalom, Call now Hushai the Archite also, and let us hear likewise what he saith.","year":-1023},{"id":"recsxSAChC1nEFrRH","ref":"2Sam.17.6","text":"And when Hushai was come to Absalom, Absalom spake unto him, saying, Ahithophel hath spoken after this manner: shall we do after his saying? if not; speak thou.","year":-1023},{"id":"recl9OC6IsYgmzor2","ref":"2Sam.17.7","text":"And Hushai said unto Absalom, The counsel that Ahithophel hath given is not good at this time.","year":-1023},{"id":"recWPDQVtW56wLqUC","ref":"2Sam.17.8","text":"For, said Hushai, thou knowest thy father and his men, that they be mighty men, and they be chafed in their minds, as a bear robbed of her whelps in the field: and thy father is a man of war, and will not lodge with the people.","year":-1023}]}
